Description: Papyrus written with black ink with demotic legal text on recto (18 ll.), verso blank. Thompson's MS Catalogue: "Petition of Tef-Hap son of Petetumis to Spemmimis prophet of Thoth and royal overseer respecting wrongs done to him by his half-brother Twot. Date year 12 Mesore 15 [of Ptolemy Philometor] = BC. 169 Sep. 15". Nos. 10575-10601 from the Siut Archive.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (48653) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/48653)
Acquisition notes: Purchased from M. Nahman. Cf. the additional sheets at the end of Thompson's MS Catalogue, titled "B.M. Nahman Papyri (1923)".
